\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Self-condensation of formaldehyde catalyzed by Ca2+ ions and borate; borate stabilizes glycolaldehyde and sugars.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Formose reaction yields glycolaldehyde, the critical C2 precursor for serine (Breslow, 1959; Patel et al., 2015). Borate minerals enhance glycolaldehyde stabilization (Patel et al., 2015).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_002\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic Photoreduction to Glycolaldehyde\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_003\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_004\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"ZnS\", \"Cu(I)/Cu(II)\", \"Phosphate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"35\u00b0C\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"ZnS, Cu(I)/Cu(II), phosphate buffer\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"UV irradiation, neutral pH\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Cu(I)/Cu(II) and ZnS photoredox catalysis reduce HCN to glycolaldehyde, driven by H2S and UV.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"HCN homologation to glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde via cyanosulfidic chemistry (Patel et al., 2015; Sutherland et al., 2017).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_003\",\n      \"name\": \"Strecker Synthesis: Glycolaldehyde + NH3 + HCN\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_002\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_005\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Montmorillonite\", \"Phosphate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"300\u2013370K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Montmorillonite, phosphate minerals\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Mildly basic pH\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Imine formation (glycolaldehyde + NH3), nucleophilic attack by HCN forms serinonitrile.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Strecker synthesis is the dominant prebiotic route to serine from glycolaldehyde, HCN and NH3; montmorillo