 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Montmorillonite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Electric spark discharge\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Spark discharge creates aldehydes and HCN, which undergo Strecker condensation to serine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Serine produced in spark discharge experiments, mechanism is Strecker pathway (Ring et al., 1972; Johnson et al., 2008; Parker et al., 2011).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_007\",\n      \"name\": \"Impact Synthesis: Serine Formation from CO2/N2\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_010\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_002\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_007\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Greigite\", \"Pyrite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"370\u2013400K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"high\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Greigite, pyrite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Meteorite impact, Fe/Ni/Mg2SiO4 minerals\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Shock impact synthesizes amino acids from CO2, N2, H2O on silicate/iron minerals.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Serine detected in meteorite impact simulations with Fe, Ni, Mg2SiO4, CO2/N2 sources (Furukawa et al., 2015; Takeuchi et al., 2020).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_008\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal Reductive Amination of Hydroxypyruvate\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_012\", \"mol_003\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_007\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Green rust\", \"Montmorillonite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"323\u2013393K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"moderate-high\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Green rust (Fe(II)), montmorillonite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Alkaline pH (9\u201311)\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Reductive amination of hydroxypyruvate with ammonia yields serine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Energetically favorable for alanine, less demonstrated for serine; plausible unde